@Node diskspare "DiskSpare"
DiskSpare is a device for improving disk capacity. Works with OS 2.04+
@EndNode

@Node ofs "OFS"
OFS means Original Filling System.  This format was the first on the Amiga.
It is slow but it works on ALL the Amigas.
@EndNode

@Node ffs "FFS"
FFS means Fast Filling System.  Developped by Commodore as a replacement of
the OFS, it is faster but it needs the ROMS 2.04 to work.  But I found the
methode for using it on Kickstart 1.2.  Contact-me if you want to know what
to do.
@EndNode

@Node dcfs "DC-FS"
DC-FS  means  Directory  Cache Filling System.  It is a filling system very
good  for  Directory  Scan  but  slow for deleting files.  Works on OS 3.0+
@EndNode

@Node pfs "PFS"
PFS  means  Professional  File  System.  It's a device used to access disks
faster than OFS.  Needs ROMS 2.04+
@EndNode

@Node ndos "NDOS"
A NDOS (No Dos) disk is a disk who is not accepted by AmigaDOS.
@EndNode

